CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1777551071
OL,3,CHealth and education: The pressures
OL,4,Cfacing the next Welsh government
OL,6,FWales' new curriculum was launched in
OL,7,F2022 and gave schools more freedom to
OL,8,Fchoose what they teach. Rather than
OL,9,Ffocus on knowledge the curriculum aims
OL,10,Fto develop general skills as well as
OL,11,Fplace an emphasis on health and well-
OL,12,Fbeing.
OL,14,FFor secondary schools, this can mean
OL,15,Fpupils start from very different
OL,16,Fbaselines. In one lesson I attended, a
OL,17,Fteacher asked her Year 7 class which
OL,18,Fperiods of history they had covered in
OL,19,Fprimary school, and it quickly became
OL,20,Fclear there was little consistency
OL,21,Fbetween them.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/19
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30205
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1777551071
OL,3,CHealth and education: The pressures
OL,4,Cfacing the next Welsh government
OL,6,F"Some of them learned different stuff
OL,7,Fto me in History," 11-year-old Mason
OL,8,Ftells me of his fellow pupils. "Some
OL,9,Fof them learned about World War I
OL,10,Fwhereas we didn't, we learned about
OL,11,FWorld War II."
OL,13,FHis classmate Madison has a similar
OL,14,Fstory about the Tudors, which other
OL,15,Fpupils had already been taught whereas
OL,16,Fher primary school had not. She says
OL,17,Fshe had to "start from the beginning"
OL,18,Fand work hard to catch up with them.
OL,26,@oD@RO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/19
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30206
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1777551071
OL,3,CHealth and education: The pressures
OL,4,Cfacing the next Welsh government
OL,6,F"The system is designed for teachers
OL,7,Fto be able to teach what they want and
OL,8,Ffor the children to do discovery
OL,9,Flearning to a certain extent," deputy
OL,10,Fhead teacher Kelly Bubbins tells me.
OL,12,F"We're finding that standards can then
OL,13,Fbe very variable when they come in to
OL,14,Four school."
OL,16,FMrs Bubbins adds that while they work
OL,17,Fvery closely with their feeder primary
OL,18,Fschools to ensure there is consistency
OL,19,Fin the curriculum, this is difficult
OL,20,Fwhen the system is designed for
OL,21,Fvariability.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/19
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30207
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1777551071
OL,3,CHealth and education: The pressures
OL,4,Cfacing the next Welsh government
OL,6,FShe says the next government needs to
OL,7,Fdecide what knowledge it wants schools
OL,8,Fto teach.
OL,10,F"We want our children to be
OL,11,Fcompetitive when they go university.
OL,12,FWe want them to be in a really good
OL,13,Fposition for the economy generally.
OL,15,F"So I think they need to look at it
OL,16,Ffrom a grassroots level and decide
OL,17,Fwhat they want the country to know,
OL,18,Fand then put that into place. At the
OL,19,Fmoment there is nothing like that,
OL,20,Fnothing like that at all."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/19
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
