OL,3,CHealth and education: The pressures
OL,4,Cfacing the next Welsh government
OL,6,FAnother concern is reading. According
OL,7,Fto their own tests conducted in
OL,8,FOctober of every year, a remarkable
OL,9,F77% of pupils arrive at Willows High
OL,10,FSchool with reading ages below their
OL,11,Fchronological age, with nearly half
OL,12,Fsignificantly behind.
OL,14,FThanks to an intensive, whole-school
OL,15,Fattempt at turning this around, only
OL,16,F49% were behind by February, but it's
OL,17,Fa big challenge.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/19
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30209
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1777551071
OL,3,CHealth and education: The pressures
OL,4,Cfacing the next Welsh government
OL,6,FDespite these shocking statistics,
OL,7,Finspection reports for primary schools
OL,8,Fin the area do not flag any concerns
OL,9,Fabout English reading, with concerns
OL,10,Fraises instead over Welsh language
OL,11,Fskills and a lack of independent
OL,12,Flearning.
OL,14,F"We aim to get to reading age 12,"
OL,15,Fsays Jessica Nelms from the English
OL,16,Fdepartment, "because that's usually
OL,17,Fwhen children can understand things
OL,18,Fand comprehend them and also read
OL,19,Ffluently."
OL,26,@vD@bO]xD@MOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/19
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30210
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1777551071
OL,3,CHealth and education: The pressures
OL,4,Cfacing the next Welsh government
OL,6,F"But we do get quite a few that are
OL,7,Fquite below that. And it does mean
OL,8,Fthat they're not understanding 70% of
OL,9,Fthe text that they're reading which is
OL,10,Fgoing to affect absolutely everything."
OL,12,FAnd this isn't a problem in one
OL,13,Fschool. International tests show Welsh
OL,14,Fpupils perform worse than those in the
OL,15,Frest of the UK in reading, maths and
OL,16,Fscience.
OL,18,FWith confusion over reading,
OL,19,Fpreviously exposed by ITV News, blamed
OL,20,Fby some for poor outcomes.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/19
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30211
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1777551071
OL,3,CHealth and education: The pressures
OL,4,Cfacing the next Welsh government
OL,6,FThis is not explained fully by higher
OL,7,Fpoverty levels in Wales, as areas with
OL,8,Fsimilar or higher levels of
OL,9,Fdeprivation in England perform better.
OL,11,FThe Institute for Fiscal Studies says
OL,12,Fthe average child in Wales performs at
OL,13,Fa similar level to poorer pupils on
OL,14,Fthe other side of Offa's Dyke.
OL,16,FIn other words, this isn't just about
OL,17,Fmoney, but also policy differences.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/19
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
